[Finding a monkey dead of yellow fever (YF), assuming that tests confirm this, is not surprising at this time of year. In Brazil, yellow fever has a seasonal pattern, based on historical analysis of human cases and epizootics due to yellow fever in the past 20 years, with 2 different periods: higher transmission occurring between December and May (seasonal period) and lower or interrupted transmission occurring between June and November. Occurrence in the Federal District is not surprising either. Cases in monkeys and humans have occurred there before. Vaccine coverage of 62% in the human population is not adequate to prevent people from becoming infected and initiating ongoing transmission in an urban human-mosquito-human cycle. - Mod.TY

